TITLE: Generating On-Scheme Colors in Bulma for Dark Mode
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to create a custom Bulma theme that generates on-scheme colors for dark mode. It imports necessary Sass modules, sets up a dark scheme main color, and then uses a loop to generate appropriate on-scheme colors for each color in the palette.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jgthms/bulma/blob/main/docs/documentation/features/dark-mode.md#2025-04-17_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
@use "sass/utilities/css-variables" as cv;
@use "sass/utilities/derived-variables" as dv;

$scheme-main-l: 11%;
$scheme-main: hsl(iv.$scheme-h, iv.$scheme-s, $scheme-main-l);

@include cv.bulma-theme($name: "my-theme") {
  @each $name, $color in dv.$colors {
    @include cv.generate-on-scheme-colors($name, $color, $scheme-main);
  }
}
```

