TITLE: Comparing Old and New HTML Structure for Form Controls in Bulma
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the changes in HTML structure for form controls. It shows how the new .field element is used as a container for labels, controls, and help text.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jgthms/bulma/blob/main/docs/_posts/2017-03-10-new-field-element.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<!-- Before -->
<label class="label">Username</label>
<p class="control has-icon has-icon-right">
  <input class="input is-success" type="text" placeholder="Text input" value="bulma">
  <span class="icon is-small">
    <i class="fas fa-check"></i>
  </span>
  <span class="help is-success">This username is available</span>
</p>

<!-- After -->
<div class="field">
  <label class="label">Username</label>
  <p class="control has-icon has-icon-right">
    <input class="input is-success" type="text" placeholder="Text input" value="bulma">
    <span class="icon is-small">
      <i class="fas fa-check"></i>
    </span>
  </p>
  <p class="help is-success">This username is available</p>
</div>
```

