TITLE: Defining Markdown Frontmatter for Blog Post
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the frontmatter for a blog post in markdown format. It includes metadata such as layout, title, introduction, color, name, and icon for the post about the new 'list of buttons' feature.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jgthms/bulma/blob/main/docs/_posts/2017-10-22-list-of-buttons.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
---
layout: post
title: "New feature: list of buttons"
introduction: "What's better than one button? Multiple buttons!"
color: "danger"
name: "List of buttons"
icon: "hand-pointer"
---
```

