TITLE: Inserting Patreon Link and Image in Markdown and HTML
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to embed a link to Bulma's Patreon page and display an image of the Patreon homepage using a combination of Markdown and HTML.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jgthms/bulma/blob/main/docs/_posts/2017-11-14-bulma-is-on-patreon.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
**Bulma** has now its own [Patreon page](https://www.patreon.com/jgthms):
```

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<figure>
  <a href="https://www.patreon.com/jgthms" target="_blank">
    <img src="{{ site.url }}/images/blog/patreon-homepage.png" alt="Bulma Patreon homepage" width="840" height="525">
  </a>
</figure>
```

