TITLE: Running Jekyll Server Command
DESCRIPTION: Command to start the Jekyll server for local documentation viewing with incremental builds and custom config file. The server will run at http://localhost:4000 and rebuild docs automatically when changes are detected.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jgthms/bulma/blob/main/docs/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
jekyll serve --incremental --config _config.local.yml
```
